deck: Gi-ne is the Saiyan mother of Goku. She and her husband, Burdock, saved their son, Kakarrot, from Freiza by sending him to Earth.
description:
Origin

Gi-ne is the wife of the Saiyan warrior-scientist, Burdock. She ran a butcher store on Planet Vegeta, the Saiyan home world; and they had two sons together, Raditz and Kakarrot.

Creation

Gi-ne (ギネ, Gine) is a supporting character of the Dragon Ball series that was created by Akira Toriyama. It first began serialization in Shueisha's Weekly Shonen Jump on December 3, 1984. She wouldn't have any appearance in the series for nearly thirty years after it began in a special one-shot chapter.

Her first appearance is in Weekly Shonen Jump No. 19 2014 #???? for a special chapter titled "Dragon Ball - Minus: Departure of the Fated Child", which was published in April 7, 2014.

As with many of the Dragon Ball series characters, Toriyama based her name after a fruit of vegetable. Gi-ne's name written backward is Negi, which in Japanese means "onion".

Character Evolution

Gi-ne's appearance in Dragon Ball is extremely brief, as she doesn't even appear in any way until nearly thirty years after the series began and nine-teen years after the series ended. In 2013, Toriyama first told a prequel story of Goku's arrival on Earth in Ginga Patrol Jaco, then an additional chapter was published in April of 2013 that explained how Goku was sent off. It was labeled as a story that even the creator didn't know about until recently.

This one-shot chapter was advertised ahead of its publication in magazines, such as Weekly Shonen Jump; and the identity of Goku's mother being revealed played a part in those promotions. Through her short appearance, Toriyama hints that Gi-ne was a kind hearted woman who cared for the well being of her children.

Major Story Arcs

Gi-ne was working at the shop when Burdock arrived, asking to see Kakarrot. He was suspicious of Frieza's recall of all Saiyan warriors, and they had a plan to save their youngest son, should the worst happen. They placed little Kakarrot into a transport ship later that same night and sent him to the small planet with little resource value called Earth. If Burdock's suspicions proved wrong, they planned to go there and find him.

Unfortunately, Gi-ne, Burdock, much of the Saiyan race, and their home planet were all destroyed by Frieza not long after.

Powers & Abilities

All Saiyans are born with an inherit strength that is known to evolve through combat. They're among many of the most fierce warriors in the universe. It's unknown what sort of combat abilities Gi-ne possessed.

Weapons & Equipment

Though seemingly not a full-time warrior, Gi-ne is shown wearing Saiyan armor.

deck: Madame Worm is a female agent of HYDRA who is composed of numerous worms beneath her beautiful guise.
description:
Creation

Madame Worm is said to be one of a number of characters created by Remender as 007-style villains for HYDRA. In an interview, he stated that the seeds of the character were first seen in Uncanny X-Men during a sequence within the World where a number of statues of previous experiments of the Weapon Plus program were shown. Among the statues present included Dr. Mindbubble and Rick Remender stated that the statue next to his was Madame Worm.
name: Madame Worm

description:
In the time that Dream of the Endless was being held prisoner by the Order of Ancient Mysteries, Magpie was one of the few denizens of the Dreaming that remained faithful to her king. Magpie was convinced that the dream king had been captured and was lucky enough to stumble into the dream of one of Morpheus' guards. She discerned his location, but everyone she tried to enlist to aid in her rescue attempt doubted her findings and elected to stay in the Dreaming and wait for their king's return.

Magpie was determined to go on her mission anyway but, being a relatively young and inexperienced dream, was unable to manifest herself in the physical realm. Instead she occupied the body of a mortal woman that happened to be near Dream's prison, and through magical interference became trapped in that body for the next 3 decades. She was eventually released from her mortal bonds by John Constantine and his allies, and returned to the Dreaming long after the king she had set out to rescue had already returned.

After returning home she assisted in the rebuilding of The House of Mystery.
name: Magpie

deck: A notorious Hong Kong crime lord was tricked in to stealing a legendary staff that gave him mystical powers but he was deemed not worthy and banished to the Capital City of Hell. After fighting his way out of the Eighth City he has vowed to use his Kung Fu to right his wrongs as the legendary Handsome Monkey King.
description:
Origin

Fifteen years ago, crime lord who calls himself the "Monkey King" was challenged by one of his men called Lion, into stealing the Ruyi Jingu Bang - the original Monkey King's bo staff and was told that if he was successful he will have all if his gold as well. The man easily swifted through all the ancient traps and was able to steal the staff only to be betrayed by his subordinate. Now trapped in the Monkey King's cave he met the original Sun Wukong and a contract was made. For stealing the staff he would receive all of the Monkey King's powers and skills but at a price: if he has true evil in his heart he will be sent to the Eighth City, (where as the seven cities before it are considered the Seven Cities of Heaven, the Eight is analogous to Hell) will burn for eternity but if he is inherently good, he will be set free. But the man was guilty of the crimes he had committed and thus was cast down to Hell with the powers and skills of the Monkey King in tow.

For fifteen years he stayed there and made Hell his personal playground. After dispatching a mob of demons, a fiery explosion occurs nearby, as one of the Worthy's Hammers has landed nearby. Armed with curiosity the Monkey King sets out to investigate the nature of this powerful impact.

His attempts to lift the hammer are met with failure, and he subsequently finds himself in the shadows of bothTitania and the Absorbing Man. Titania though possessed by the being known as Skirn, Breaker of Men, it is revealed the she actually knows of Sun Wukong from times, past. She attacks him, allowing Creel the chance to claim the hammer. His contact with it, transforming him into Greithoth: Breaker of Wills.

Later the Monkey King travels back to Hong Kong and gets and takes down the crime syndicate now run by Lion and traps him in the same hell he was once trapped in. After seeing the error of his ways he vows to right wrongs and protect Hong Kong.

Current Events

Currently Monkey King has joined the The Ascendant and joins in the attack on Madripoor to help the Avengers take back the country from Gorgon and The Hand.

Powers

The Monkey King was blessed with some of the powers of the original Sun Wukong. He has super strength, speed and agility. He is a master martial martial artist and uses his staff to full effect. He's also able to shape shift in to various animals like an eagle, frog and a lion.
